To run the test suite, you must first add the following variables into your .env file (must be .env, .env.local or any other variant will not work):

PLAYWRIGHT_SUPABASE_SECRET_KEY
ADMIN_USERNAME
ADMIN_PASSWORD

The first variable will be the supabase secret key. You can find this in the supabase project settings under "API Keys".
The second variable, ADMIN_USERNAME, will be the username you use to log into the website.
The third variable, ADMIN_PASSWORD, will be the password you use to log into the website.

Once you have added these environment variables, you can run 'npx playwright test' in the root directory of the project to run the tests.

You can also use 'npx playwright test --ui' to view the tests in UI mode (see https://playwright.dev/docs/test-ui-mode for more information).